# intent-classification-system

## Core Intent Classification Engine 
Importance Score: 95/100

Located in `backend/src/agents/contextManager.ts`:

- Eight distinct workflow types:
  - Brainstorming: Open-ended ideation sessions
  - Deciding: Evaluation and selection of options
  - Modifying: Refinement of existing items
  - Exploring: Research and investigation
  - Reviewing: Analysis and assessment
  - Development: Technical implementation details
  - Parking: Deferral of items for later
  - General: Default catch-all workflow

- Classification signals:
  - Keyword pattern matching
  - Context history analysis
  - User intent markers
  - Previous workflow state
  - Agent feedback loops

## Workflow Orchestration
Importance Score: 90/100

Located in `backend/src/agents/orchestrator.ts`:

- Dynamic agent selection based on classified intent
- Conditional execution paths:
  - Verification required for decisions
  - Clarification needed for ambiguous input
  - Review triggered for major changes
  - Citation checks for factual claims

- State transitions:
  - Exploring -> Deciding -> Parked
  - Draft -> Review -> Approved
  - Question -> Clarified -> Resolved

